# Ignore local Claude Code state (settings.local.json, session data). Keep only
# the shared, versioned MARKDOWN under .claude/skills and .claude/commands: the
# subtree is ignored by default, then just directories + *.md are re-included,
# so arbitrary nested files (settings.local.json, *.sqlite, caches, deps, logs,
# secrets) are never force-tracked past the repo-wide ignores.
.claude/*
!.claude/skills/
.claude/skills/**
!.claude/skills/**/
!.claude/skills/**/*.md
!.claude/commands/
.claude/commands/**
!.claude/commands/**/
!.claude/commands/**/*.md
# Re-ignore vendored/generated subtrees under the tracked assets. A skill or
# command may grow deps or reports (node_modules, coverage, dist); without these
# a parent-dir ignore, the `*.md` negations above would force-track third-party
# READMEs and generated reports. An excluded parent dir wins over the file rule.
.claude/skills/**/node_modules/
.claude/skills/**/coverage/
.claude/skills/**/dist/
.claude/commands/**/node_modules/
.claude/commands/**/coverage/
.claude/commands/**/dist/
# The /improve skill writes implementation plans here as markdown; surface them
# to git instead of letting the global *.md rule hide (and silently lose) them.
!plans/
!plans/**/*.md
!advisor-plans/
!advisor-plans/**/*.md
